Title:
Niger River Basin

Description:
The Niger is the third longest river in Africa, and has the ninth largest river basin in the world. It rises in Guinea, in the Fouta Djallon hills ("the water tower of West Africa"), and flows first to the northeast, almost to the edge of the Sahara in Mali.
